2. Clean the "API_Endpoint" Column¶

Separate the API_Endpoint based on {http_request_method} /{api_version}/{api_endpoint_method}. Remove any trailing duplicated slashes in the column.

In [4]:
items = log_df['api_endpoint'].str.split('/',expand=True)
log_df['action'] = items[0]
log_df['version'] = items[1]
log_df['end_point'] = items.iloc[:,2:].fillna("").apply(lambda x: '/'.join(x), axis=1)
log_df.drop(['api_endpoint'],axis=1,inplace=True)

#Write the function to remove trailing duplicated characters
def remove(str):
    if not str or len(str)==0:
        return str
    lst=list(str)
    i,j=0,0
    while j < len(lst):
        if lst[j] != '/' or (j != 0 and lst[j-1] != '/'):
            lst[i]=lst[j]
            i+=1 
        j+=1
    if i > 0 and lst[-1]=='/':
        i -= 1
    return ''.join(lst[:i])

for i in xrange(13336):
    log_df['end_point'][i] = remove(log_df['end_point'][i])

3. Clean the “The_Date" Column¶

Clean the date by transforming it into standard year-month-day format. Though not required in this data analysis, I still identify the weekday, year, month and day for possible future data exploration, like identifying the weekly and monthly pattern of API usage.

In [5]:
log_df['date']= pd.to_datetime(log_df['the_date'])
log_df['weekday'] = log_df.date.dt.weekday_name

day_order = ['Monday','Tuesday','Wednesday','Thursday','Friday','Saturday', 'Sunday']

log_df['weekday'] = pd.Categorical(log_df['weekday'], categories=day_order, ordered=True)
log_df['year'] = log_df.date.dt.year
log_df['month'] = log_df.date.dt.month
log_df['day'] = log_df.date.dt.day
log_df.drop(['the_date'],axis=1,inplace=True)
log_df.head()

4. Download the CSV File¶

Download the CSV and further analyze and visualize the data in Spark platform.

In [6]:
from IPython.display import HTML
import base64  
def create_download_link(df, title = "Download CSV file", filename = "new_daily_logs.csv"):  
    csv = df.to_csv()
    b64 = base64.b64encode(csv.encode())
    payload = b64.decode()
    html = '<a download="{filename}" href="data:text/csv;base64,{payload}" target="_blank">{title}</a>'
    html = html.format(payload=payload,title=title,filename=filename)
    return HTML(html)

create_download_link(log_df)
